reviews.review_text:
a very good example This is a very good example as to why a good audience recording is far and away better than a great sbd. That which provides the supernatural quality at a gd show is the energy which is produced between the band and the crowd. Without it all you have is half the story. A matrix is preferable but, I'll take a really good aud. over a sbd. anyday.
Check out the way the heads react to the explosions (especially towards the end of Althea) its priceless. Also, an in your face Passenger well worth the listen.

review below nailed it... anyone ever try a matrix of 80% AUD 20% SBD

***seems like a good idea on paper***

Outstanding show I was fortunate enough to have a high school friend that when to the University of Hartford from 79-83. He got us front row tickets for this show. This is a very solid show all the way around. 

This recording and remixing really bring out the best of everything. As has been said many times - Thank you CM.

The second set is one of my favorites. The China-> Rider is stellar. The five song seg following is exceptional. Comes a Time was a rare treat and was a nice change of pace after the explosive first few songs to open the set. 

This is definitely worth a listen
The Bass IMHO the Bass on this show is overwhelming.
cowbell please Jerry is plugged in China Cat through Comes A Time in a big way. Comes A Time carried so much power at this stage. Jerry was airborne to end the Rider.
